    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - REMOVE - INTEGRAL OIL PUMP</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="7">
        <title>INTEGRAL OIL PUMP</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the two bolts holding the oil tube in position (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300771">Figure 71</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300771" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300771" filename="../figg13/G1300771.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 71. Remove Oil Tube</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the oil tube (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300771">Figure 71</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Straighten the tube lock on the suction tube (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300772">Figure 72</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300772" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300772" filename="../figg13/G1300772.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 72. Straighten Tube Lock</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the suction tube from the oil pump (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300773">Figure 73</hotlnk>). If necessary, remove the O-ring from the suction tube.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300773" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300773" filename="../figg13/G1300773.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 73. Remove Suction Tube From Oil Pump</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove three Allen head bolts and washers that retain the integral oil pump to the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300774">Figure 74</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300774" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300774" filename="../figg13/G1300774.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 74. Remove Bolts and Washers Retaining Integral Oil Pump to Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the integral oil pump assembly from inside the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300775">Figure 75</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300775" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300775" filename="../figg13/G1300775.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 75. Remove Integral Oil Pump Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the integral oil pump retainer plate from inside the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300776">Figure 76</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300776" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300776" filename="../figg13/G1300776.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 76. Remove Integral Oil Pump Retainer Plate</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If necessary, the front case plug can be removed from the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300777">Figure 77</hotlnk>). To remove, insert a bar from inside the case and tap the
                plug out.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300777" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300777" filename="../figg13/G1300777.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 77. Remove Front Case Plug</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the plug O-ring and replace if damaged (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300777">Figure 77</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
